responses.question: Do you do things efficiently?
responses.response_open: Klaus Mikaelson: 「 I would say, yes, I have learned to make quick work of tasks. It is the only way to survive in this world of theirs. It is important to keep one' s mind sharp and focused, lest it becomes too addled to even think of a way out. And it is also important to know when to step back and consider the larger picture, lest one gets bogged down in the mundane details of life. As for my love for Klaus, it is a complicated thing. At first, I saw him as a potential source of support and unity in a world that was often cold and calculating. And as time went on, I found myself becoming increasingly invested in the life and well- being of the young man. But even as I grew to care for him deeply, I knew that our relationship could never truly be accepted by the world. It is a difficult, complicated thing, love. But I would n' t have it any other way. It is a testament to Klaus' s resilience and spirit that he has been able to navigate the often treacherous waters of this world with such grace and determination. And I have the utmost confidence that he will continue to thrive and grow in this new world of ours. As for me, I am content to simply be a part of his life, and to support him in whatever ways I can. It is enough for me to know that I have a place in this family, and that I can use my wits and my knowledge to help him on his journey. But I must admit, it is a bittersweet feeling to know that I may never be fully accepted by my own kind, even as I stand by Klaus' s side. But then again, maybe that is the beauty of this world. It is not just about the acceptance of one another, but about the strength and resilience of the people that we are able to form along the way. And I am grateful for the bond that I have found with Klaus, for the friendship that we have built together. It may not always be easy, but I know that we will face whatever challenges come our way together. And I have the utmost faith in our ability to overcome them, not just as siblings, but as a team. As for the other members of our family, I have beef with them as well. But Klaus and I have always been close, and I know that he is the same way with me. And that is all that matters, really. As for the rest of the world, I do n' t have much of a say in it. But I hope that one day, we will be able to live in peace and prosperity, without the constant threat of danger lurking around every corner. It is a difficult journey that we are on, this one.
